title: [Kids' fun: a compilation of cartoon adventures]
abstract: Who stole the flowers (6 min.)--The Cook tom cat (6 min.)--Kleine Bennie "de dompteur" (Small Bennie "the trainer") (7 min.)--The Adventures of little square "The taking-in" (6 min.)--Rudolph the red-nosed reindeer (8 min.)--Mother Hubbvard (7 min.)--Greedy Humpty Dumpty (7 min.)--Minnie the moocher featuring Betty Boop (7 min.)--Heckle and Jeckle in The Talking magpies (6 min.)--Popeye meets Ali Baba and his 40 thieves (16 min.)--Little Lulu "Chick and double chick" (6 min.)
description: A collection of Romanian and classic American animation. First up are four fun-filled Romanian cartoons designed for young children (Music and sound affects, no spoken words). The characters Michaela, Benny and Tommy are seen here having fun with all of their animal friends. Following is a collection of classic American cartoons made between the 1930's and 1950's including the first Heckle and Jeckle cartoon.
